## Description {#details}

Lightweight arrays that are backed by an arbitrary BinaryStream.

This file provides two different array implementations. 

<CodeBlock>
VarStreamArray - Arrays of variable length records.  The user specifies
  an Extractor type that can extract a record from a given offset and
  return the number of bytes consumed by the record.

FixedStreamArray - Arrays of fixed length records.  This is similar in
  spirit to ArrayRef&lt;T&gt;, but since it is backed by a BinaryStream, the
  elements of the array need not be laid out in contiguous memory.
</CodeBlock>

<Link id="l00054" /><CodeLine lineNumber="54"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">/// VarStreamArray represents an array of variable length records backed by a</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00055" /><CodeLine lineNumber="55"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">/// stream.  This could be a contiguous sequence of bytes in memory, it could</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00056" /><CodeLine lineNumber="56"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">/// be a file on disk, or it could be a PDB stream where bytes are stored as</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00057" /><CodeLine lineNumber="57"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">/// discontiguous blocks in a file.  Usually it is desirable to treat arrays</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00058" /><CodeLine lineNumber="58"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">/// as contiguous blocks of memory, but doing so with large PDB files, for</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00059" /><CodeLine lineNumber="59"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">/// example, could mean allocating huge amounts of memory just to allow</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00060" /><CodeLine lineNumber="60"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">/// re-ordering of stream data to be contiguous before iterating over it.  By</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00061" /><CodeLine lineNumber="61"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">/// abstracting this out, we need not duplicate this memory, and we can</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00062" /><CodeLine lineNumber="62"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">/// iterate over arrays in arbitrarily formatted streams.  Elements are parsed</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00063" /><CodeLine lineNumber="63"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">/// lazily on iteration, so there is no upfront cost associated with building</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00064" /><CodeLine lineNumber="64"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">/// or copying a VarStreamArray, no matter how large it may be.</span></CodeLine>
